on\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Apr 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xzo1697451500520.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xzo1697451500520.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xzo1697451500520.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xzo1697451500520\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The default timeout to connect to a Sentinel RMS server is 30 seconds. If the RMS server\n\t\tdoes not respond within that time, Uniface will stop trying and report an error. But 30\n\t\tseconds may be too long or too short, so <code class=\"ph codeph\">LM_TIMEOUT</code> can be used to set a\n\t\tdifferent timeout (in seconds).</p>\n<p class=\"p\">However, when <code class=\"ph codeph\">LM_REDUNDANT</code> is used, the timeout is set to just one second. The\n\t\t\treason for this is that if the RMS server that was initially assigned the role of leader\n\t\t\tis down, then the login to a license feature will wait the full timeout period to get\n\t\t\tits license from the original leader, and only when that has expired try to get it from\n\t\t\tthe actual leader. Since Sentinel allows minimum one second time,\n\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">LM_REDUNDANT</code> will use this time as the duration for network\n\t\t\ttimeout. However, if you have a slow or busy network, one second may be too short. If\n\t\t\tone second is too short, then you may experience errors that you do not get if you do\n\t\t\tnot use <code class=\"ph codeph\">LM_REDUNDANT</code>. You can increase <code class=\"ph codeph\">LM_TIMEOUT</code> to\n\t\t\ttwo or more seconds to solve this situation.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">An example for a pool of three redundant RMS servers on a slow network:</p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$license_options LM_LICENSE_FILE=rms.serverA;rms.serverB;rms.serverC, LM_REDUNDANT,\n\t\t\t\tLM_TIMEOUT=2</code></p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6653614\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6653614\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "LM_TIMEOUT Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Apr 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The default timeout to connect to a Sentinel RMS server is 30 seconds. If the RMS server does not respond within that time, Uniface will stop trying and report an error. But 30 seconds may be too long or too short, so LM_TIMEOUT can be used to set a different timeout (in seconds). However, when LM_REDUNDANT is used, the timeout is set to just one second. The reason for this is that if the RMS server that was initially assigned the role of leader is down, then the login to a license feature will wait the full timeout period to get its license from the original leader, and only when that has expired try to get it from the actual leader. Since Sentinel allows minimum one second time, LM_REDUNDANT will use this time as the duration for network timeout. However, if you have a slow or busy network, one second may be too short. If one second is too short, then you may experience errors that you do not get if you do not use LM_REDUNDANT . You can increase LM_TIMEOUT to two or more seconds to solve this situation. An example for a pool of three redundant RMS servers on a slow network: $license_options LM_LICENSE_FILE=rms.serverA;rms.serverB;rms.serverC, LM_REDUNDANT, LM_TIMEOUT=2 Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}